      <span>CHEW BEFORE YOU SWALLOW</span><span class="sep"> &nbsp;·&nbsp; </span>
      <span>YOUR FEED CHOSE YOU</span><span class="sep"> &nbsp;·&nbsp; </span>
      <span>THAT EMOTION WAS SCHEDULED</span><span class="sep"> &nbsp;·&nbsp; </span>
      <span>VERIFY BEFORE YOU AMPLIFY</span><span class="sep"> &nbsp;·&nbsp; </span>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ══ TOPIC 1 ══ -->

<div class="sec sec--blue fade">
  <div class="sec-num">01</div>
  <span class="tag">Topic 01</span>
  <h2 class="sec-h">THREE<br><span class="hl">FLAVOURS</span><br>OF FALSE</h2>
  <p class="body-txt">Not all fake is the same. Before you react — know which one you're dealing with.</p>

  <div class="flavours">
    <div class="flavour-item f-mis">
      <div class="flavour-name">MISINFORMATION</div>
      <div class="flavour-def">Shared wrong. No bad intent. They just didn't check.</div>
      <div class="flavour-eg">your aunt forwarding a health myth she fully believed 💌</div>
    </div>
    <div class="flavour-item f-dis">
      <div class="flavour-name">DISINFORMATION</div>
      <div class="flavour-def">Made up on purpose. There's a plan behind it.</div>
      <div class="flavour-eg">a bot network flooding feeds before an election 🤖</div>
    </div>
    <div class="flavour-item f-mal">
      <div class="flavour-name">MALINFORMATION</div>
      <div class="flavour-def">Actually true — but used as a weapon to destroy someone.</div>
      <div class="flavour-eg">leaking someone's private photos to ruin their reputation 📵</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="pull">
    intent is everything.
    <span class="pull-attr">— the one thing to remember</span>
  </div>

  <div class="tip"><p>When you see something false: does the person sharing it <em>know</em> it's false? If not — correct gently. If yes — don't engage. Amplifying disinformation, even to debunk it, spreads it further.</p></div>
</div>

<div class="rip rip--lc"></div>

<!-- ══ TOPIC 2 ══ -->

<div class="sec sec--lace fade">
  <div class="sec-num" style="color:var(--blue)">02</div>
  <span class="tag">Topic 02</span>
  <h2 class="sec-h">NEWS ISN'T<br>FOUND.<br><span class="hl">IT'S BUILT.</span></h2>
  <p class="body-txt">Someone chose every word you just read. Every story has four invisible hands shaping it.</p>

  <div class="news-grid">
    <div class="news-card">
      <div class="news-card-num">01</div>
      <div class="news-card-name">SELECTION</div>
      <p>Why THIS story — and not the 1000 others that happened today?</p>
    </div>
    <div class="news-card">
      <div class="news-card-num">02</div>
      <div class="news-card-name">FRAMING</div>
      <p>"Riot" or "protest"? Same event. Very different story.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="news-card">
      <div class="news-card-num">03</div>
      <div class="news-card-name">OMISSION</div>
      <p>What's NOT in the story is as powerful as what is.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="news-card">
      <div class="news-card-num">04</div>
      <div class="news-card-name">AUDIENCE</div>
      <p>Who is this made for? That changes everything about how it's told.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="pull" style="color:var(--blue);border-color:var(--orange);">
    "language is never innocent."
    <span class="pull-attr" style="color:var(--blue);">— Stuart Hall, cultural theorist</span>
  </div>

  <div class="tip"><p>Five questions for any media: Who made it? What techniques did they use? How might someone else read this differently? What values does it push? Why now?</p></div>
</div>

<div class="rip rip--bl"></div>

<!-- ══ TOPIC 3 ══ -->

<div class="sec sec--blue fade">
  <div class="sec-num">03</div>
  <span class="tag">Topic 03</span>
  <h2 class="sec-h">THE<br><span class="hl">MANIPULATION</span><br>TOOLKIT</h2>
  <p class="body-txt">These tricks are almost 100 years old. They still work on you — because they bypass logic and go straight for emotion.</p>

  <div class="toolkit">
    <div class="tool-item">
      <div class="tool-n">01</div>
      <div class="tool-body">
        <div class="tool-name">BANDWAGON</div>
        <div class="tool-def">Pressure to join because everyone else already has.</div>
        <div class="tool-eg">"9 out of 10 people in your area have already switched..." 🐑</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tool-item">
      <div class="tool-n">02</div>
      <div class="tool-body">
        <div class="tool-name">FEAR APPEAL</div>
        <div class="tool-def">Exaggerates a threat so you stop thinking and start reacting.</div>
        <div class="tool-eg">"If you don't act now, your family will be at risk." 😨</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tool-item">
      <div class="tool-n">03</div>
      <div class="tool-body">
        <div class="tool-name">PLAIN FOLKS</div>
        <div class="tool-def">Powerful people pretend to be ordinary to seem trustworthy.</div>
        <div class="tool-eg">the billionaire eating at McDonald's for the cameras 📸</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tool-item">
      <div class="tool-n">04</div>
      <div class="tool-body">
        <div class="tool-name">NAME CALLING</div>
        <div class="tool-def">Attach a label to someone. Now you don't have to hear their argument.</div>
        <div class="tool-eg">dismissing critics as "radical" without engaging them once 🏷️</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tool-item">
      <div class="tool-n">05</div>
      <div class="tool-body">
        <div class="tool-name">GLITTERING GENERALITIES</div>
        <div class="tool-def">Vague positive words that sound great but mean absolutely nothing.</div>
        <div class="tool-eg">"Freedom. Family. Values." — impossible to disagree with, impossible to define ✨</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tool-item">
      <div class="tool-n">06</div>
      <div class="tool-body">
        <div class="tool-name">TRANSFER</div>
        <div class="tool-def">Link yourself to something already respected. Borrow its credibility.</div>
        <div class="tool-eg">politician speaks in front of the national flag. says nothing new 🚩</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="pull">
    knowing the name slows you down by one second.<br>that second is enough.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="rip rip--lc"></div>

<!-- ══ TOPIC 4 ══ -->

<div class="sec sec--lace fade">
  <div class="sec-num" style="color:var(--blue)">04</div>
  <span class="tag">Topic 04</span>
  <h2 class="sec-h">CHECK IT.<br><span class="hl">THEN</span><br>SHARE IT.</h2>

  <div class="stat-big">6×</div>
  <p class="stat-label">False news travels 6 times faster than true news on social media. You are part of that chain. — MIT, 2018</p>

  <div class="sick-grid">
    <div class="sick-card">
      <div class="sick-letter">S</div>
      <div class="sick-name">SOURCE</div>
      <p class="sick-desc">Where did this originally come from? Is there a primary source?</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sick-card">
      <div class="sick-letter">I</div>
      <div class="sick-name">IMAGE</div>
      <p class="sick-desc">Reverse image search that photo. Old images are recycled constantly.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sick-card">
      <div class="sick-letter">C</div>
      <div class="sick-name">CORROBORATE</div>
      <p class="sick-desc">Is anyone else reporting this? One source = suspicious.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sick-card">
      <div class="sick-letter">K</div>
      <div class="sick-name">KNOW YOUR BIAS</div>
      <p class="sick-desc">Are you sharing because it's true — or because it confirms what you already think?</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="pull" style="color:var(--blue);border-color:var(--orange);">
    "sharing a false story makes you part of the story."
    <span class="pull-attr" style="color:var(--blue);">— Craig Silverman, misinformation researcher</span>
  </div>

  <div class="tip"><p>Before you share anything that made you angry, sad, or shocked — pause. Those are the three emotions disinformation is engineered to trigger. Tools: <strong>Snopes · FactCheck.org · TinEye · Google Images</strong></p></div>
</div>

<div class="rip rip--or"></div>

<!-- ══ THE REACTION LAB ══ -->

<div class="sec sec--blue fade">
  <div class="sec-num">05</div>
  <span class="tag">Interactive</span>
  <h2 class="sec-h">THE<br><span class="hl">REACTION</span><br>LAB</h2>
  <p class="body-txt">Five headlines. One question each: what emotion were they designed to trigger in you? Just play. No score.</p>

  <div class="lab-wrap">
    <div class="lab-header">
      <h3>🧪 THE REACTION LAB</h3>
      <div class="lab-counter"><span id="labDone">0</span> / 5 done</div>
    </div>
    <div class="lab-progress"><div class="lab-progress-fill" id="labFill"></div></div>
    <div class="lab-instr">Read the headline. Tap the emotion it was <em>designed</em> to make you feel. Then see why it works.</div>
    <div class="lab-cards" id="labCards"></div>
  </div>
</div>

